eNCA’s Lethiwe Mdluli reports. #dstv403 DURBAN - ANC president, Cyril Ramaphosa has kicked off his campaign trail in KwaZulu-Natal. He's visiting the province this weekend and encouraging people to register to vote ahead of the general elections next year. Residents have raised all kinds of service delivery issues during his visit. Ramaphosa says their electricity woes will become a thing of the past now that there’s a new minister tasked with ending the country’s power crisis. eNCA’s Lethiwe Mdluli reports.